.Dd April 19, 2026
.Dt MPORT.LIST 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm mport.list
.Nd list installed packages, updates, origins, or locks
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl b
.Op Fl c Ar chroot-path
.Op Fl l
.Op Fl o
.Op Fl p
.Op Fl q
.Op Fl u
.Op Fl U
.Op Fl v
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
prints installed package information from the local package database.
It is the low-level helper used by
.Xr mport 1
for list-oriented output.
.Bl -tag -width ".Fl U"
.It Fl b
Use brief output.
.It Fl c Ar chroot-path
Run inside the specified chroot.
.It Fl l
List locked packages.
.It Fl o
Include package origins in the output.
.It Fl p
List only explicitly installed packages.
.It Fl q
Use quiet output.
.It Fl u
Show installed packages with updates available.
.It Fl U
Do not load or refresh the package index for update information.
.It Fl v
Use verbose output.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
List installed packages:
.Dl $ mport.list -v
.Pp
List installed packages with available updates:
.Dl $ mport.list -u
.Pp
List locked packages:
.Dl $ mport.list -l
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr mport 1
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility appeared in
.Mx 0.3 .
